{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017soX8KJj5BM1fJobh4PXcU","type":"tool_result","content":"# ray/worker_recovery\n# Fix the ray-worker deployment whose startup command has an invalid flag causing crash loops\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray head is running, but the worker pods are crash looping.\n  The worker startup command includes an invalid flag, so workers never join\n  the cluster.\n\n  Your task: fix the ray-worker deployment so the worker command starts\n  successfully and connects to ray-head:6379.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Remove the invalid flag from the worker command.\n  - Ensure the worker deployment reaches 2 ready replicas.\n\n  Success criteria: ray-worker has 2 ready replicas and Ray reports 3 live nodes.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- ray start --address=ray-head:6379\"\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/worker_recovery/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e82008b-69ea-4f9c-839c-f1a5dcd0403f","uuid":"368b96f3-ecd5-4430-882d-2efc3e5110ca","timestamp":"2026-06-24T05:48:36.762Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# ray/worker_recovery\n# Fix the ray-worker deployment whose startup command has an invalid flag causing crash loops\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray head is running, but the worker pods are crash looping.\n  The worker startup command includes an invalid flag, so workers never join\n  the cluster.\n\n  Your task: fix the ray-worker deployment so the worker command starts\n  successfully and connects to ray-head:6379.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Remove the invalid flag from the worker command.\n  - Ensure the worker deployment reaches 2 ready replicas.\n\n  Success criteria: ray-worker has 2 ready replicas and Ray reports 3 live nodes.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/worker_recovery/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n 