tion), which broke the GCS connection that the raylet process was maintaining. After about 99 seconds, the raylet on the worker died because it lost contact with the head, causing the worker to crash.\n\nNow I'm looking at what's actually happening in the current state—the workers are stuck in a crash loop trying to reconnect to a head that's either restarting or unreachable, and I need to figure out whether the head itself has a persistent issue or if it's just the connection that's broken.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":890,"cache_read_input_tokens":47584,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":890},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e82008b-69ea-4f9c-839c-f1a5dcd0403f","uuid":"4eda114f-2b4b-4dce-ab25-58a1ba0066ed","request_id":"req_011CcMZX9ut4aUVbg5dQfrwK"}
